testprocedure.test-case-summary: This test procedure is called by a test case and is used to verify the SUTs support of the dlIntersectionSignalPriorityQueueRequest dialog as an OC using variables provided by the calling test case. This procedure supports verification of requirements related to user need 2.3.5.10.6 [Need to View Traffic Signal Controller Plan Queue] and is used for both valid and invalid test cases.

testStep.functionId: Step 1 CONFIGURE: Determine the Application Layer Standard that will be used for this test. RECORD this information as: ApplicationLayerStandard: ${ApplicationLayerStandard}

Step 2 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Restrictions - Device Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.1.7.2.2.1). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N91R432_Restrictions___Device_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N91R432_Restrictions___Device_Queue_Supported}

Step 3 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Operator Identifier - Device Queue Acknowledge is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.1.7.2.2.2). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N91R433_Operator_Identifier___Device_Queue_Acknowledge_Supported = ${TMDD_N91R433_Operator_Identifier___Device_Queue_Acknowledge_Supported}

Step 4 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Unique Sequence Number is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.1.7.2.2.3). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N91R434_Unique_Sequence_Number_Supported = ${TMDD_N91R434_Unique_Sequence_Number_Supported}

Step 5 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Event Identifier - Device Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.1.7.2.2.4). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N91R435_Event_Identifier___Device_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N91R435_Event_Identifier___Device_Queue_Supported}

Step 6 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Event Response Plan - Device Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.1.7.2.2.5). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N91R436_Event_Response_Plan___Device_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N91R436_Event_Response_Plan___Device_Queue_Supported}

Step 7 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Request Start Date and Time - Device Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.1.7.2.2.6). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N91R437_Request_Start_Date_and_Time___Device_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N91R437_Request_Start_Date_and_Time___Device_Queue_Supported}

Step 8 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Request Expiration Date and Time - Device Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.1.7.2.2.7). Step 9 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Signal Timing Mode - Signal Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.11.13.3.2.1). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N91R1099_Signal_Timing_Mode___Signal_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N91R1099_Signal_Timing_Mode___Signal_Queue_Supported}

Step 10 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Signal Timing Pattern - Signal Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.11.13.3.2.2). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N91R1100_Signal_Timing_Pattern___Signal_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N91R1100_Signal_Timing_Pattern___Signal_Queue_Supported}

Step 12 CONFIGURE: Define the message that will be sent to the SUT. RECORD this information as: RequestMessage: ${RequestMessage}
Step 13 CONFIGURE: Determine whether an error response message is expected for this test. RECORD this information as: ErrorResponseExpected: ${ErrorResponseExpected}
Step 14 CONFIGURE: IF ErrorResponseExpected is true, determine the expected error code response for this test. RECORD this information as: ErrorTypeExpected: ${ErrorTypeExpected}
